MISSILE WEAPONS
---------------

Missile weapons can be used to fire ammunition.  The ammunition type must
match the missile weapon.  A sling fires pebbles and shots, a bow fires
arrows and a crossbow fires bolts.  Missile weapons can't be thrown for
damage.

When firing ammunition with a missile weapon, the to-hit and to-dam bonus of
that weapon are added to the bonuses of the player and the missile.  The
damage done is then multiplied by the power of the missile weapon, as shown
in the table below.

Example: A player with a to-dam bonus for shooting of +5 shoots non-magical
arrows with a Long Bow (x3) (+2,+2).  The damage is (1d4 [arrow] +2 [bow]
+5 [player]) x3 [bow].  Mininum damage is 24 hit points, maximum is 33.

