ARMOR
-----

A character can wear up to six pieces of armor on different body parts: on
body (body armor or a robe), about body (a cloak), on arm (a shield), on
head (a cap, helmet or crown), on hands (gloves, gauntlets or cesti) and on
feet (boots).  Each of these types of armor has its own list.  Dragon armor
is a special type of body armor; it is dealt with in a separate section
following this one.

